Justine Bateman https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Justine_Bateman 0 Justine Tanya Bateman (born February 19, 1966) is an American writer, director, producer, and actress. Her acting work includes the 80s hit Family Ties, Satisfaction, Men Behaving Badly, The TV Set, Desperate Housewives, and Californication. Five Minutes, the film short she wrote, directed, and produced, premiered at the 2017 Toronto Film Festival. Justine earned her Computer Science and Digital Media Management degree from UCLA in 2016.
